---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GlobalNav from '../components/GlobalNav.astro';
import GlobalFooter from '../components/GlobalFooter.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Revenue Engine Method: Memory, Intelligence, Motion | Treetop"
  description="Treetop's method for installing a revenue engine that compounds. Three phases: Memory (what your growth system knows), Intelligence (how it thinks), Motion (what it does about it)."
  canonicalUrl="https://treetopgrowthstrategy.com/methodology"
>
<script type="application/ld+json" slot="schema">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "The Revenue Engine Method",
  "description": "The three phases Treetop uses to install a revenue engine that compounds: Memory, Intelligence, Motion.",
  "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Bill Colbert", "url": "https://treetopgrowthstrategy.com/about" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Treetop Growth Strategy" },
  "mainEntityOfPage": "https://treetopgrowthstrategy.com/methodology"
}
</script>

<style>
  .lbl { font-size:0.68rem; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#00C853; margin-bottom:1.25rem; display:block; }
  .btn-p { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:6px; background:#00C853; color:#050D05; padding:0.875rem 1.75rem; font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600; text-decoration:none; border:none; cursor:pointer; transition:opacity 0.2s,transform 0.15s; white-space:nowrap; }
  .btn-p:hover { opacity:0.88; transform:translateY(-1px); }
  .btn-g { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:6px; background:transparent; color:#F0FFF0; padding:0.875rem 1.75rem; font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600; text-decoration:none; border:1px solid #1A3A1A; transition:border-color 0.2s,background 0.2s; }
  .btn-g:hover { border-color:rgba(0,200,83,0.4); background:rgba(0,200,83,0.05); }
  .rule { width:100%; height:1px; background:#1A3A1A; }
  .phase { background:#050D05; border:1px solid #1A3A1A; padding:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem; transition:border-color 0.2s; }
  .phase:hover { border-color:rgba(0,200,83,0.35); }
  .phase-num { font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif; font-size:0.9rem; font-style:italic; color:#00C853; letter-spacing:0.08em; }
  .phase-h { font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif; font-size:clamp(1.6rem,3.2vw,2.4rem); font-weight:400; color:#F0FFF0; line-height:1.15; margin:0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .phase-body { font-size:0.98rem; color:#8FAF8F; line-height:1.8; margin-bottom:1.25rem; }
  .phase-body strong { color:#C0D8C0; font-weight:500; }
  .phase-inst { font-size:0.85rem; color:#4A6A4A; line-height:1.7; padding:1rem 1.25rem; border-left:2px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.35); background:#0A1A0A; margin-bottom:1.25rem; }
  .phase-inst em { color:#00C853; font-style:normal; font-weight:500; }
  .phase-links { display:flex; gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap; font-size:0.85rem; }
  .phase-links a { color:#00C853; text-decoration:none; border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.3); padding-bottom:1px; }
</style>

<GlobalNav active="methodology" />

<!-- HERO -->
<section style="min-height:70vh;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;padding:7rem 2.5rem 4rem;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:1000px;margin:0 auto;width:100%;">
    <span class="lbl">The Revenue Engine Method</span>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(2.6rem,5.5vw,4.4rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.08;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:1.75rem;letter-spacing:-0.01em;max-width:900px;">
      Three phases. One engine that compounds.
    </h1>
    <p style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:300;color:#8FAF8F;max-width:720px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2rem;">
      Most marketing functions grow by accretion. A tool here, a freelancer there, an agency in between. What starts as scrappy becomes random acts of marketing, and the compounding never begins. The Revenue Engine Method is how we build the alternative.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:0.98rem;color:#C0D8C0;max-width:720px;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      Every engine we install goes through the same three phases, in this order, because skipping one breaks the next. Memory before Intelligence, Intelligence before Motion.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="https://calendar.app.google/GS5H5y8U3PrN8u4A8" class="btn-p">Book a strategy call &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/pricing" class="btn-g">See the ladder &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="rule"></div>

<!-- PHASE 1: MEMORY -->
<section style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-num">Phase 01</div>
      <h2 class="phase-h">Memory. What your revenue engine knows.</h2>
      <p class="phase-body">
        Memory is the ground truth your growth machine is standing on. Who you sell to, what they buy, why they buy, what the last 100 customers had in common, what your competitors are actually doing this quarter, which channels have returned real dollars, which have quietly lit money on fire. Most companies do not have this in one place. It is scattered across a CRM nobody trusts, a spreadsheet a former ops person owned, and the founder's head.
      </p>
      <p class="phase-body">
        <strong>Without Memory</strong>, every decision is a fresh guess, every hire has to learn the same things again, and the AI you buy has nothing to reason over. With it, the engine finally has a state, not just a stream of tasks.
      </p>
      <div class="phase-inst">
        <em>What installing Memory looks like:</em> we pull your competitive landscape, your search footprint, your CRM, and your revenue history into one place, and produce a written diagnosis you can act on. This is the Diagnose group of the ladder.
      </div>
      <div class="phase-links">
        <a href="/pricing#diagnose">Diagnose your engine (Starter Report + Revenue Engine Audit) &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PHASE 2: INTELLIGENCE -->
<section style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-num">Phase 02</div>
      <h2 class="phase-h">Intelligence. How your engine thinks.</h2>
      <p class="phase-body">
        Intelligence is the layer that takes Memory and turns it into decisions. What do we do about the fact that we now know where we stand? Which levers do we pull first, and how do we tell if it is working? This is where AI actually earns its keep. Not to draft another blog post, but to keep the diagnosis current, watch the competitors, spot what changed, and put a priority on the founder's desk each week that is grounded in the data, not vibes.
      </p>
      <p class="phase-body">
        <strong>Without Intelligence</strong>, Memory becomes a snapshot that ages badly and never gets looked at again. With it, the engine gets more useful every month it runs.
      </p>
      <div class="phase-inst">
        <em>What installing Intelligence looks like:</em> the always-on productized layer of the ladder. We keep the diagnosis alive with monthly refreshes, what-changed memos, and a strategist on call. This is the Run group of the ladder.
      </div>
      <div class="phase-links">
        <a href="/pricing#run">Run your engine (Monitor, Guided, Embedded) &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PHASE 3: MOTION -->
<section style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-num">Phase 03</div>
      <h2 class="phase-h">Motion. What your engine actually does.</h2>
      <p class="phase-body">
        Motion is the doing. Campaigns going out on schedule, sales sequences firing, deals moving through stages, content shipping, hires being made, budgets landing on channels that work. The most common failure mode we see is companies with a lot of Motion and almost no Memory or Intelligence underneath it. That is not a growth engine. That is expensive noise. The right Motion is the natural output of Memory plus Intelligence, and it only compounds when a real leader owns the number.
      </p>
      <p class="phase-body">
        <strong>Without Motion</strong>, the smartest diagnosis in the world sits in a slide deck. With it, and with a leader accountable for the outcome, growth becomes a system your team can execute even when you are not in the room.
      </p>
      <div class="phase-inst">
        <em>What installing Motion looks like:</em> a fractional CMO or CRO takes ownership of the number, runs the plan, hires and manages the doers, and reports weekly on what moved. This is the Lead group of the ladder.
      </div>
      <div class="phase-links">
        <a href="/pricing#lead">Lead your engine (Fractional CMO or CRO) &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="rule"></div>

<!-- WHY IN THIS ORDER -->
<section style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="lbl">Why the order matters</span>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.6rem);font-weight:400;color:#F0FFF0;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      Skip a phase and the next one breaks.
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Skip Memory and Intelligence is guessing with confidence. You will hire an agency that runs the same playbook as the last one, or buy an AI tool that summarizes the wrong data faster. Skip Intelligence and Motion becomes churn. Campaigns go out on themes instead of insights, and nobody knows which ones actually moved the number. Skip Motion and the whole thing sits in a Google Doc.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.8;">
      The three phases are not a menu. They are a build order.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="rule"></div>

<!-- FINAL CTA -->
<section style="padding:6rem 2.5rem;background:#050D05;text-align:center;">
  <div style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="width:80px;height:3px;background:#00C853;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;"></div>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3rem);font-weight:400;color:#F0FFF0;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Ready to install the engine?
    </h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      A 30-minute strategy call is the fastest way to see whether the Method fits your situation. No pitch, no deck. We look at where you are, decide whether you need to Diagnose, Run, or Lead first, and go from there.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="https://calendar.app.google/GS5H5y8U3PrN8u4A8" class="btn-p">Book a strategy call &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/quiz" class="btn-g">Take the Revenue Engine Scorecard &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<GlobalFooter />

</Layout>
